parameters:
\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(As Phils-san mentioned, there are several people
who seem to be magicians... For now, let's listen
to what they have to say.
\n<Mage-like man>Yeah, but what do you need?

\OC[31]\N<Rain>I was wondering if you could examine the magical
power trapped within this fragment. Is that
possible?

\CE[79]\n<Mage-like man>\....\....\....\. What's this? I don't feel any
magical power at all though?

\CE[79]\n<Mage-like man>Oh, are you testing me by any chance? If I answer
about magical power with this, you'll say that I'm
a fake magician, right?

\n<Mage-like man>Sigh... There it is, there it is. Occasionally you
come across people like that. Well, the truth is,
there are many who pretend to be full-fledged
magicians even though they can't really do much. I
can't say I don't understand the feelings of
someone like you.

\n<Mage-like man>But seriously, can't you tell just by looking at
me? I'm clearly a professional magician, right?
Don't lump me together with those half-assed guys.

\n<Mage-like man>I'm a professional, you know? If you're asking a
professional for help, it's only natural that
there would be a proper compensation, right?

\n<Mage-like man>So? That fragment is just trash, but what's your
real business? Well, since I'm a professional, I
expect to be properly compensated.

\CE[78]\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>No, I will let you know another time. Sorry for
the trouble.

\CE[79]\n<Mage-like man>Oh well. Ah~ If you establish a connection with me
now, you'll regret it in the future. Well, you
don't seem to have good judgment anyway, so it
doesn't really matter.

\CE[78]\CE[79]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(As I heard, there are a lot of people with
unfavorable impressions here..........

\EMP This town is so low-level. It's all about
appearances and lacks substance.

\EMP Sigh, it seems like nobody here understands.
There doesn't seem to be anyone who can see
through my true abilities.

\N<Adventurer-like Man B>Being in a 'bukkake' state reduces agility and
critical hit rate. And it also increases sexual
desire easily. That smell, it kinda makes me
horny, haha.

\N<Woman who seems like an adventurer B>You can buy materials obtained from monsters and
things caught in dungeons at \C[17] stalls, but
the prices are clearly a rip-off. \C[0] Well, I
guess there's a perspective of buying convenience
with money, but even so, it's too expensive.

\N<Man A who looks like an adventurer>Hmm, I was caught off guard because my agility was
lowered due to being in a 'sticky' state... It's
troublesome when my agility is low because it
allows the enemies to take the initiative...

\N<Man A who looks like an adventurer>I need to make sure not to forget
\C[17]\NI[23]\C[0] in the next adventure. With
that, I can cure the 'bukkake' state and it's
surprisingly useful.

\N<Woman who looks like an adventurer A>Um, the 'paralysis' status decreases attack power,
agility, and evasion, but it will be lifted after
the battle... However, since the duration is long,
it would be faster to recover with \C[17]\NI[20]
or \C[0]...
\EMP Oh? When did you end up in a brothel...?

\EMP Hey there, cutie... Pour me lots of drinks~
Hiccup...

\EMP Hey, this request is about the sea. How about
staying overnight as well?

\n<Male Magician>Hm? Ah, yeah. Are you a swordsman? Are you looking
for party members, by any chance?

\OC[31]\N<Rain>I'm looking for a magician who can investigate the
magical power trapped in this fragment. What do
you think?

\CE[79]\n<Male Magician>Investigation? Ah~ I'm afraid that's not my thing.
I specialize in offensive magic, so I don't do
those kind of subtle tasks.

\CE[78]\CE[84]\n<Male Magician>Hey, instead of that, why don't we form a party
together? It would be so much fun exploring any
dungeon with a beautiful person like you! Don't
you think?

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>No, it's fine. I apologize for intruding so
suddenly. Excuse me.

\n<Male Magician>Wait, hold on! \. It'll definitely be fun, so
let's team up~!

\EMP Well, I wonder if there are any easy money-
making requests today... Hmm...

\EMP Geez, if you're not gonna form a party with
me, then forget it!

\EMP That sounds good, maybe I should buy a new
swimsuit~

\EMP That's why! I worked so hard, so I should be
given a bonus, right? It's so inflexible!

\EMP Hey, when do you finish work? Let's go out
for a drink. Of course, I'll treat.

\EMP The receptionist girl, she's taking quite a
while to finish her work. Well, I'll wait for her
patiently.
\CE[79]\n<A man like a magician>Huh?... Oh? Oh? What's this? You're so cute!

\n<A man like a magician>What do you need from me? Well, never mind. Let's
just grab a bite to eat and talk! I know a great
place!
\CE[79]\CE[84]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Uh, well, sorry, I'm in a bit of a hurry

\n<A man like a magician>Never mind that! What's your name? Ah, I heard
this town has high-level people, and it's true!
I'm glad I came here.

\n<A man like a magician>Huh? Well, I'm not an adventurer. I just dressed
up like this to meet an adventurer girl, but
doesn't it look the part?

\CE[78]\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I'm sorry, but I'm looking for a magician, so
I'll take my leave.

\n<A man like a magician>It's fine, let's just grab a bite to eat for now!
Come on!

\CE[78]\CE[79]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner
Rain>(Mistaking me for a regular person and not an
adventurer... \. Am I tired?)

\EMP Oh, there's a nice-looking restaurant in this
town. Maybe I should invite some girls and check
it out!
\EMP Ugh, it's just a meal. Stop being so stingy!

\EMP Surely you don't intend to go on an
adventure dressed like that...?

\EMP Sigh, that adventurer is really persistent. I
wonder if they'll really wait until I finish
work... Scary.

\EMP U-um... even though it's free to dress for
adventure, could you please refrain from exposing
yourself so much...

\EMP Thanks to the selfish adventurer, I have to
work overtime again... sigh, I wonder if something
good will happen...
